July 03, 2020

Temporal Discounting Social Distancing Study 1

Age distribution

The sample ranged in age from 18 to 86 with a mean age of 52.53.

Sex distribution

The sample had 117 women (50.21%).

Education distribution

The vast majority participants had some college (81.5%).

Race distribution

The samples were almost equally distributed between White (36.1%), Black (30%), or Hispanic/Latino (36.1%).

Income distribution

The most frequent income band selected was $20,000-$29,999.

The median income band was $60,000 - $70,000

Employment distribution

The most frequent employment was Yes, has paid employment: Full time employee (30 hours a week or more).

34.76% were employeed full time.

31.76% were retired.

Class distribution

The most frequent class was Middle class, 48.93%.
